.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH dialog 1  "dialog " 
.SH NAME
dialog \- Browser dialog handling (alert, confirm, prompt, beforeunload)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdialog\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Detect and handle browser JavaScript dialogs (alert, confirm, prompt, beforeunload). Query whether a dialog is open, accept or dismiss it, and provide prompt text. Useful for automation scripts that need to respond to dialogs programmatically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
dialog\-handle(1)
Accept or dismiss the current browser dialog
.TP
dialog\-info(1)
Check whether a dialog is currently open
.TP
dialog\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  # Check if a dialog is open
  agentchrome dialog info

  # Accept an alert or confirm dialog
  agentchrome dialog handle accept

  # Dismiss a dialog
  agentchrome dialog handle dismiss

  # Accept a prompt with text
  agentchrome dialog handle accept \-\-text "my input"
.SH CAPABILITIES
.PP
Browser dialog handling (alert, confirm, prompt, beforeunload)
.TP
.B dialog handle
Accept or dismiss the current browser dialog
.TP
.B action
Action to take: accept or dismiss
.TP
.B --text
Response text for prompt dialogs (only used with 'accept' action)
.TP
.B dialog info
Check whether a dialog is currently open
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Examples:
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog info\`
Check if a dialog is currently open
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept\`
Accept an alert or confirm dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle dismiss\`
Dismiss a dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept --text "my input"\`
Accept a prompt dialog with text
